14. Self-application

The deepest version is internal.

Your own mind throws frames at you all day.
	•	“I’m behind.”
	•	“I ruined it.”
	•	“They must think…”
	•	“This means I am…”

Run the same scan.

What is the claim?
What assumption makes it work?
What pressure comes with it?
What invariant would restore clarity?

That turns the system inward without becoming self-deception.

