15. The compact doctrine

Here is the distilled form:

Not every question deserves an answer.
Not every frame deserves entry.
Name the assumption.
Slow the tempo.
Choose the invariant.
Move the terrain.

That is the engine.

⸻

16. The even tighter operator card

When pressure hits, remember:

What frame is this?
Who benefits if I accept it?
What standard is being smuggled in?
What cleaner standard survives after the heat is gone?

Then answer from there.

